===Verb===
{{en-verb}}

#{{avalent}} Of rain: To fall from the sky.
#:''It will rain today.''
#{{intransitive}} To fall in large quantities.
#:''Bombs rained from the sky.''
#{{transitive}} To [[issue]] (something) in large quantities.
#:''The boxer rained punches on his opponent's head.''

